						               													<description>One of the typical classes in the subject of Monsters is to create a Frankenstein. In order to do that, we just have to find the suitable body parts and sew them following the correct pattern.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To be able to create our monster, the first thing to do is to find the suitable pieces. Each player shall take theirs. Keep in mind that each body piece has two different sides.&amp;#10;Once we have all the body pieces, we take the thread and... let's sew!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;We shall join the pieces together in a way that the thread at the top seam coincides with our card pattern. We can pass the thread up to 3 times through the same hole. Look the pattern closely and make sure that there aren't more or fewer threads.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When a player has finished their monster shouts 'It's alive!'. The rest of the players check the seams and, if they are correct, that player is awarded Student of the Month. However, if there's any mistake, the game continues and the player shall fix the possible errors.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There's no turn order.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
